Listen, I really don't feel like it,
but he had an issue with the check.

249
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:22,600
Because it turns out Shani gave you a check
from a book that was in her bag that got lost.

250
00:12:23,080 --> 00:12:25,760
Then she found it
but forgot she canceled it.

251
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,440
So no...

252
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:30,160
By chance, I have a new checkbook here, so I...

253
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:34,360
I'll exchange it.
-Sure, sure.

254
00:12:37,040 --> 00:12:38,280
Awesome.

255
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:45,600
From...

256
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,080
From...

257
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,240
From a guy.
You know
b-l-y

258
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:55,560
That's it.
-Thank you very much.

259
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:57,280
I love celebrations.

260
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,040
I always say, only for celebrations.

261
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:01,960
It's a shame they didn't throw marshmallows, licorice.

262
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:03,680
Hey, is there a chance you could give the kid

263
00:13:03,760 --> 00:13:05,440
your car keys?
-No.

264
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:07,440
No, not that I have anything against it,

265
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:09,240
we just need to go to my parents' later,

266
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,600
my dad isn't feeling too well.

267
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:12,240
What's wrong with him?
-He...

268
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:14,000
Had a follow-up visit,

269
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:15,640
they wanted to give him antibiotics through an IV.

270
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,480
The bourekas have arrived, sorry.

271
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:23,760
Look at Alin and Manny, on cloud nine, huh?
-Of course they're on cloud nine,

272
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:27,200
they got 200 dollars from Efrat,
she sent them from America via UPS.

273
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:30,600
What?
-You know, from that company, U-P-S.

274
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:31,600
Say?
Poo-aah
Wuu l'

275
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:33,600
Yeah. And what do you call that together?

276
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:35,240
Oops.
-Here you go.

277
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,920
What do you say, she sent them 200 dollars?

278
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:37,840
200 dollars.

279
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:39,800
Wow, that's nice.

280
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:43,240
What is that? How much is 200 dollars?

281
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,720
Oops.

282
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,400
A lot, a lot...

283
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:48,920
Shai, come here.

284
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,160
Why?
-Come here for a sec.

285
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,640
It turns out Efrat sent 200 dollars.
-So?

286
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:55,720
So what? I’m not ready to be the stingy sister.

287
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:59,280
I could put in more but I put in less
because of the coordination and what's customary.

288
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:01,560
Which apparently isn't customary at all,
if you send 200 dollars via UPS.

289
00:14:01,640 --> 00:14:02,960
Don't you think you're exaggerating a bit?

290
00:14:03,040 --> 00:14:04,120
I don't understand what difference it makes,

291
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:07,200
it's just a gift for your brother
and his wife for their little boy,

292
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:10,880
your sweet nephew, right?
-No. What matters is that I don't look bad.

293
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:14,160
So now you're going to Manny and you're
exchanging the check for its original amount.

294
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:15,240
When?
-Guess.

295
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:20,960
Orna, is there a chance you could give me
your car keys?

296
00:14:21,040 --> 00:14:22,240
Do you think?

297
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,880
I've been waiting an hour for someone to come replace me.

298
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:25,320
Now you’ll go in for him right away.

299
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:27,400
Do you think?
-Oh, yeah?

300
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:29,400
You know what? Instead of bourekas
I'm serving childhood photos of you.

301
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,680
Move!

302
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,080
What?

303
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,120
What?

304
00:14:39,880 --> 00:14:40,920
What?

305
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,280
What?

306
00:14:44,160 --> 00:14:47,360
Yeah, Shai. Thanks a lot, Sabta, perfect timing.

307
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:51,680
Listen, it’s really not my thing,
but it’s actually, surprisingly funny.

308
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:55,520
The check I wrote, the pen, the girl gave it to me.

309
00:14:55,880 --> 00:14:57,360
So what turns out now? It’s really funny,

310
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:01,000
the pen is one of those magic pens
that disappears after a few minutes.

311
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,520
Disappears?
-Yeah.

312
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:04,080
So it’s pointless to write a blank check, you know,

313
00:15:04,280 --> 00:15:05,640
the bank won’t find that funny.

314
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,720
What a thing, let me see.
-No, what’s there to see?

315
00:15:07,800 --> 00:15:09,960
Sabta wants to say goodbye.

316
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:17,280
What?

317
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:18,920
What?

318
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:21,920
What?

319
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:25,200
What?
-What’s up?

320
00:15:25,800 --> 00:15:28,120
The check, it’s written.

321
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:29,560
Thanks.

322
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:33,680
Goodbye...
-Is everything okay?

323
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,680
What’s up, Dad, how’s your voice?

324
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:42,960
The voice and everything is just fine, it’ll pass in no time.

325
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:44,560
See you.

326
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:47,400
He says a lot of livelihood and blessings.

327
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:49,120
What’s this, you’re translating them all day?

328
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:50,920
I’m not translating, after so many weeks with them

329
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:52,680
I know exactly what he wants to say.

330
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:56,440
Wow, good for Efrat, right?
She sent them 200 dollars.

331
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,760
Mom, what’s he saying? I don’t understand.

332
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:09,360
He says it’s not that she sent them 200 dollars

333
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:13,320
but that she owed Alin
100 dollars from her last visit.

334
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,440
What does that have to do with anything now?

335
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:23,040
I don’t understand what he’s saying.
What did he say? I didn’t get it.

336
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:27,560
What’s there to understand? On her last visit
she swallowed the card at the ATM

337
00:16:27,640 --> 00:16:30,080
so Alin lent her 100 dollars, that’s it.

338
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:33,520
Oops.

339
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:36,600
Okay. Shai.
-And if you see him, tell him

340
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:39,000
it’s not nice that he spreads
all kinds of lies about his dad.

341
00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:41,560
He’s not spreading any lies,
his dad really isn’t feeling well.

342
00:16:45,320 --> 00:16:47,400
What, you wanted a bourekas?
-Meirav!

343
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:49,480
Sorry, I finished them all.

344
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:52,120
It’s okay, just make another tray.
-Where to?

345
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:54,360
Where to? To Tavor.
-I’m not doing that.

346
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,240
Everyone even laughs at me for burning salad.

347
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:58,040
Salad!
Burnt!
How can you...
-Exactly!

348
00:16:58,120 --> 00:16:59,480
Enough, Zizi, Zizi, enough, I’ll do it.

349
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,960
Ah, 'Naf', I see you’re managing.

350
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:05,599
I wonder if Yonatan is still here. Yonatan.

351
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,720
Shai.
-What now? I’m making bourekas.

352
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:11,119
I understand and I’m sorry
but we need to break the check again.

353
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:13,760
But I already changed it.
-Right, but we need to break it again.

354
00:17:13,839 --> 00:17:15,920
What break it again? I’m making bourekas.

355
00:17:16,599 --> 00:17:17,800
Honey, what’s going on with you?

356
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:20,800
At first, we brought a nice gift,
you asked to make it smaller? Fine,

357
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:23,079
then you asked to make it bigger, also fine,

358
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,000
now you want to make it smaller again?
-Yeah.

359
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:28,119
Why?
-Because it turns out Efrat owed Alin 100 dollars

360
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,080
and that’s not part of the gift,

361
00:17:29,280 --> 00:17:32,720
So it turns out I'm putting my sisters in a bad light again, you know?

362
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:37,040
Forget it, I'll make bourekas at home.

363
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:38,200
Alright, son...

364
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:41,560
Aunt Chava.

365
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:43,240
Ohhh
Ohhh

366
00:17:43,320 --> 00:17:46,080
Can I please have your car keys?
-What?

367
00:17:46,480 --> 00:17:47,520
Mmm.

368
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:49,720
Mmm.

369
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:52,840
Mmm.

370
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:54,680
Mmm.

371
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:56,640
What now?
-Listen.

372
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:57,560
No way.

373
00:17:58,680 --> 00:17:59,720
You know what, forget it,

374
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:00,840
Just give me that check.

375
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:03,600
I'm writing you an open check here

376
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,760
and a pen that works,

377
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:12,640
I'll call you with the amount
as soon as your crazy sister gets her act together.

378
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:14,760
Goodbye.
-Goodbye, Bulshoi.

379
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:18,000
Yeah, Dad, hi.

380
00:18:18,480 --> 00:18:20,680
Hello, Shayka, we’re back home,

381
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:23,640
can you pass me Shabi's dad?
-Sure, no problem.

382
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:27,320
Silvan, here, my dad wants to say congratulations.

383
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,080
Son, he’ll say it, they’re waiting.

384
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:33,920
Hello.

385
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:36,440
Hello?

386
00:18:37,480 --> 00:18:39,320
Hello, hello, hello.

387
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:41,840
Alright...

388
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:44,760
Dad, he can't really talk right now.

389
00:18:44,840 --> 00:18:48,080
So pass me the lady.
-Please.

390
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:51,520
What’s this, he doesn’t want to talk to you?
-Why wouldn’t he want to talk to me?

391
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:57,040
Maybe he’s upset you didn’t come,
they get upset over everything.

392
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:59,600
Sensitive, sensitive.
-Hello, Pinchas.

393
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,120
Riki, she can hear you.

394
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:03,760
Hello, Racheli. Hi, how are you?

395
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:07,600
Everything's fine. Tell Riki
we weren't offended that you didn’t come,

396
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:09,400
we just really missed you.

397
00:19:09,960 --> 00:19:14,040
I heard you fell, not on us.
-Not on you, on the table.

398
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:16,840
I got on a chair to take down a vase from up high

399
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:19,760
and then I fell and hit my head on the table.

400
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:23,120
Nothing serious, just a few small cuts.
-I.

401
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:25,600
Just a second, hold on.

402
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:27,760
That’s it, Mom, we’re leaving.
-Alright, sweetie.

403
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:29,440
Have a good week.

404
00:19:32,320 --> 00:19:33,160
Thanks.

405
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,440
Bye, Dad.
-Bye, bye, bye.

406
00:19:36,280 --> 00:19:39,640
Yeah, Pinchas, I’m with you. Everything okay with you?

407
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,280
Yeah, yeah, all good.

408
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:46,880
But then, while in the ER, I fainted
into the cleaner's bucket with bleach

409
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,800
and inhaled too many fumes.
-What are you saying...

410
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:52,880
Turns out there's this health organization of fainting people

411
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,160
that’s going around all the hospitals now.

412
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:58,520
At least they figured out what it is and you’re okay?
-Of course I’m okay,

413
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:00,200
they gave me an antibody shot.

414
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:02,920
And did the shot help?
-Of course it helped,

415
00:20:03,280 --> 00:20:07,960
just in the syringe of the antibody shot
there was a tiny bubble,

416
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:11,800
so they took me for a CT to make sure
that bubble didn’t reach my head.

417
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,640
The test came back normal, I hope.

418
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:16,440
Mom.
-Just a second, hold on.

419
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:18,520
Alright. That’s it! Mom, we’re going.

420
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:19,880
Yes, yes.
“Yachin Y...

421
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:21,920
Have a good week, congratulations.
-Good week.

422
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,240
Congratulations, sweetie.
-Bye, Abalia.

423
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:24,640
“Yachin, yes.

424
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:25,880
Yes, Pinchas, I’m with you.

425
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:27,480
Totally fine.

426
00:20:27,640 --> 00:20:30,080
There was a concern about meningitis.

427
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:32,920
But the dean came out, as you say in your place,

428
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:35,600
Knock on wood, knock on wood, hamsa, hamsa, hamsa.

429
00:20:35,760 --> 00:20:37,560
We don’t say that here,

430
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,120
But I get what you mean.

431
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:44,080
So lots of congratulations, and again, we apologize.

432
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:46,200
Thank you so much, Pinchas! Feel better, lots of health.

433
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:48,520
Say hi to Riki. Bye.

434
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:51,400
Oh my, we’re leaving, it was really nice.
-Bye.

435
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:52,680
I organized what I could in the kitchen.
-Shabbat shalom.

436
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:53,600
Is everything okay?

437
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:55,440
Thank you so much, Marinka, thanks.
-Thanks.

438
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:57,440
Silvio.

439
00:20:58,880 --> 00:20:59,880
I have no words.

440
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:04,680
I’ll talk to you tomorrow, bye.

441
00:21:11,560 --> 00:21:12,440
Thank you.

442
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,080
No problem.

443
00:21:16,440 --> 00:21:19,840
You drove me crazy with that voice of yours,
you’ve been driving me nuts all day.

444
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:21,840
No, no, it’s passing, it’s passing.

445
00:21:23,160 --> 00:21:24,040
Okay, I need a bourekas.

446
00:21:24,120 --> 00:21:26,040
What? Yoad is Tzvika the cross-eyed guy's son?

447
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,120
Wow, poor Meirav.

448
00:21:29,840 --> 00:21:31,080
Alon's brother?

449
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:33,440
What are you saying?

450
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:35,480
What does he have on the way, "Dad's bourekas"...

451
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:38,120
Do you remember if "Miriam's bourekas" is open on Shabbat?

452
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:39,280
Well, may he have good health.

453
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:41,040
There's also that guy from TV.

454
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:43,320
Alright, babe. Let’s go, bye.

455
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:45,080
There’s a problem.
-What?

456
00:21:45,160 --> 00:21:46,040
You won’t believe it.

457
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,200
What now? Aunt Chava is there more than us?

458
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:49,400
No, Alin's brother.

459
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:52,240
Come on, we need to go back.
-No, we don’t need to go back.

460
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:54,160
Of course we need to, what do you mean "don’t need"?
-Don’t worry.

461
00:21:54,840 --> 00:21:57,920
Promise this is the last week?
-Yeah, I already know how everyone is fat.

462
00:21:58,040 --> 00:21:59,360
So here, I’m calling Manny.

463
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:04,000
Too bad I didn’t leave the whole notebook with him.

464
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:07,880
See you.

465
00:22:09,120 --> 00:22:11,840
He said lots of blessings and livelihood.

466
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:13,400
What’s that?

467
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:16,280
I’m sorry. Bye.

468
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:18,560
Again, again, from the beginning.

469
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,400
From the beginning.

470
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:26,240
There was a little bubble in the syringe that went to my head.

471
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:28,120
And they took me for a CT to check that...

472
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:31,960
They had an air bubble in the syringe
of the antibodies, so they took him for a CT

473
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:34,280
to make sure the bubble didn’t reach the head.

474
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:35,560
Okay.

475
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:37,680
What are you saying, Alin's brother.

476
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:40,880
What a weirdo.

477
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,920
What does he have on the way?
-No, no weirdo, what...

478
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:44,000
Yeah, I don’t know what’s wrong with me.

479
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:46,400
Can you swap Grandma Chava with the bourekas?

480
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:47,960
I’m already tired.

481
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:51,160
What’s this, Grandma? You’re an aunt, honey,
why on earth would you say Grandma, honey?

